        Leather Working Group

        Leather Working Group is a not-for-profit multi-stakeholder organization committed to reducing the environmental impact of leather manufacturing. It sets the LWG Standards of environmental criteria against which leather manufacturers are independently audited and certified. A product highlighting Leather Working Group means the brand can verify all the leather used in that product comes from an LWG-certified facility.

        Product Description

        Carina l is taking inspiration from styles from the 80's - interpreted to fit today's laid-back sneaker look of californian beach towns. The leather upper is accented by a perforated vamp and a PUMA formstripe. The highlight of the shoe is the new cupsole tooling though with a slightly elevated platform sole with texture interest in toe and heel area and cat branding in the medial. The SoftFoam plus sockliner provides superior cushioning and optimal comfort for every step of your day. Lace closure for a snug fit

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        Learn more how customers reviews work on Amazon

        Customers say

        Customers find these sneakers comfortable, with one mentioning they walk without pain, and appreciate their trendy style and quality. The fit receives mixed feedback - while some say they fit great, others find them too tight in the toe box and too large in the heel area. Moreover, customers consider them a good value for money, particularly as a cheaper alternative to white shoes. However, durability is a concern, with multiple customers reporting that the shoes fell apart within three months of use.

          5.0 out of 5 stars Comfy, Cute, Def Size Up!!
          Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2024
          Size: 8.5Color: White-white-silverVerified Purchase
          Im pretty solidly a size 8 - every now and then an 8.5 depending on the shoe, but thats pretty rare. Based on reviews, I sized these up to an 8.5 and theyre okay - a little snugger than Id usually like but not bad enough to make me return and exchange. But if I were to do so, Id size all the way up to a 9. So SIZE UP A FULL SIZE, NOT JUST A HALF.

          Orherwise, Ive worn them for ~3 weeks now to work (at a public school), on vacation (in nice hotels and through the woods to the airbnb), to run errands, to church, to friends houses, and to go out to eat. Theyre great for any outfit! Theyre comfortable with great cushion! No break-in time needed! Through the white sneaker shopping phase, I read a lot about sneaker backs being rough on the ankle/achilles area and even with pre-existing blisters from other shoes still healing on both my Achilles zones, they werent bothered at all by these shoes! Im more a no-show sock girly, but these look good with no-shows AND ankle socks! (Im sure they look good with crew and tall socks, too, thats just not my style.) They look cute with athletic shorts/fits, denim shorts and dressy shorts outfits, dresses, and slacks!

          I also have a terrible track record with keeping white shoes clean and white, but these have been great! Ive only accumulated a few scuff marks and dirt zones on the shoes after near-daily wear over 3 weeks and they clean easily with magic eraser (brand name or generic) sponges!
